    "difficulty": "Intermediate",
    "whatItDoes": "expo/use-dom lets you run React web components inside a webview on iOS and Android while rendering them natively on web. Add the 'use dom' directive to a file and it works with web-only libraries like recharts or react-syntax-highlighter without rewriting anything. Props passed from native code are serialized automatically, and async functions become a bridge between the webview and native APIs.",
